Survey under the Ministry of Environment of Lithuania: 1) neotectonically active faults, 2) borings, 3) hydrogeological borings, 4) groundwater bodies, 5) hydrogeological objects, 6) underground water monitoring facilities and borings, 7) seismic monitoring stations, 8) Lithuanian Quaternary geological map M 1:200 000, 9) Lithuanian geomorphological map M 1:200 000, 10) Lithuanian Pre-Quaternary geological map M 1:200 000, 11) Hydrogeological map M 1:200 000.The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement> This dataset contains land cover data of the Lithuania from the European CorineLandCover 2018 dataset (CLC2018). CLC products are based on photointerpretation of satellite images by national teams of participating countries - the EEA member and cooperating countries – following a standard methodology and nomenclature with the following base parameters: 44 classes in the hierarchical three level Corine nomenclature; minimum mapping unit for status layers is 25 hectares; minimum width of linear elements is 100 metres. It has been harmonized according to INSPIRE.</gco:CharacterString>      </gmd:abstract>      <gmd:pointOfContact>        <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>          <gmd:organisationName> – the Coastal Research and Planning Institute of Klaipeda University . <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Species Distribution theme is created using state information system of Protected species data in Lithuania. State Service for Protected Areas under the Ministry of Environment of the Republic of Lithuania is the manager of data. Mininstry of Environment is the manager of state information system. The purpose of the information system is to collect and systematize data about protected species and their habitats and make it available to interested parties.Due to sensitivity and importance of data, input data of protected species is summarised and aggregated by 10 km grid cells in the result data set. The number of individuals in grid cell is indicated. Data values are coded according to international classification. European Workshop on Reference Grids in 2003 and later INSPIRE geographical grid systems. Three vector polygon grid shape files, 1, 10 and 100 km, are available. The grids cover country borders - plus 15km buffer - and marine Exclusive Economic Zones - plus 15km buffer. Note that the extent of the grid into the marine area does not reflect the extent of the territorial waters.The reference grids are based on ETRS89 Lambert Azimuthal Equal Area projection. <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Area Management/Restriction/Regulation Zones and Reporting Units theme is created using input data sets:  1) landfills and waste collections (source of data – Spatial data set of (geo) reference base cadastre (GRPK)), data provider – the Ministry of Agriculture of the Republic of Lithuania; 2) noise zones of agglomerations, 3) main roads, and 4) railways, data provider – the Ministry of Health of The Republic of Lithuania; 5) plant health zones, data provider – the State Plant Service; 6) Sea region, data provider – the Coastal Research and Planning Institute of Klaipeda University; 7) air quality management zones and agglomerations, 8) river basins, and 9) nitrate sensitive areas, data provider – the Environmental Protection Agency; 10) protected areas for drinking water, 11) karst areas (data source – the Map of Lithuania's karst zone boundaries 1:50,000), 12) mineral resources, and 13) underground water resources, data provider – Lithuanian Geological Survey under the Ministry of Environment of Lithuania; 14) forest management zones, data provider – the State Forest Service.The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality> about actual measurements of precipitation, air temperature, wind speed, and wind direction for the territory of Lithuania. Meteorological Geographical Features theme is using input data sets provided by Lithuanian Hydrometeorological Service under the  Ministry of Environment of the Republic of Lithuania: 1) map of meteorological observation stations, 2) actual measurements of precipitation; 3) air temperature, 4) wind speed and direction, 5) relative humidity, 6) historical measurements of precipitation, 7) historical measuments of air temperature.   Actual weather data is updated hourly. In case of disruptions, is updated not later than in 4 hours. Past data about weather conditions is updated according to the need. </gmd:identifier>        </gmd:CI_Citation>      </gmd:citation>      <gmd:abstract>        <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Statistical Units theme represents information about the current Statistical grid ETRS89 of the Republic of Lithuania and current area of statistical administrative units. This statistical grid has three different cell sizes: 1x1 km, 10x10 km and 100x100km. Statistical grid cells have unique codes. These codes allow the creation of links between INSPIRE data themes, such as Population Distribution – Demography and Statistical Unit themes.This dataset represents the current area of statistical administrative units: 1) NUTS1 (boundaries and area of Lithuania), 2) NUTS2 (boundaries and area of Capital region and Central and Western Lithuania region), 3) NUTS3 (boundaries and areas of counties), 4) LAU (boundaries and areas of districts). Statistical administrative units have unique codes.</gco:CharacterString>      </gmd:abstract>      <gmd:pointOfContact>        <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>          <gmd:organisationName> <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>Inspire dataset for Sea Regions theme is created using input data sets: 1) coastal line (data source – Georeference Spatial Data Set of the Territory of the Republic of Lithuania at scale 1:250 000 According to the Requirements of the International Project EuroRegionalMap EuroRegionalMap 1:250,000), data provider – the National Land Service under the Ministry of Agriculture of the Republic of Lithuania; 2) bottom biotopes, 3) the thickness of Quaternary sediment distribution and Quaternary bedrock, the lithological composition of bottom sediments, and 3) pollution sources and dispersion in the Lithuanian Baltic Sea, data provider – the Coastal Research and Planning Institute of Klaipeda University.The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage> monitoring facilities and borings, 7) seismic monitoring stations, 8) Lithuanian Quaternary geological map M 1:200 000, 9) Lithuanian geomorphological map M 1:200 000, 10) Lithuanian Pre-Quaternary <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Natural Risk Zones theme is created using input data sets:  1) social, cultural and natural objects located in flood hazard zones, 2) coastal flooding risk areas, and 3) flooding risk areas caused by sknowmelt runoff and rainfall, data provider – Environmental Protection Agency; 4) data of karst areas (data source – Map of Lithuania's karst zone boundaries 1:50,000), and 5) data of risk places (data source – Map of risk places in Vilnius and Kaunas), data provider – Lithuanian Geological Survey under the Ministry of Environment of Lithuania; 6) Cultural Heritage Registry, data provider – Department of Cultural Heritage under the Ministry of Culture; 7) State Cadastre of Protected Areas of the Republic of Lithuania, data provider – State Service for Protected Areas under the Ministry of Environment; 8) buildings and landfills (data source – Georeference spatial data set for the territory of the Republic of Lithuania 1:50,000 (GDR50LT)), data provider – National Land Service under the Ministry of Agriculture; 9) Spatial data set of (geo) reference base cadastre (GRPK), data provider – the Ministry of Agriculture of the Republic of Lithuania. The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>  </gmd:dataQualityInfo></gmd:MD_Metadata>

      </gmd:CI_Citation>      </gmd:citation>      <gmd:abstract>        <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Environmental Monitoring Features theme represents information about environmental elements (including atmospheric, surface and sub-surface, underground water, territorial water in the Baltic Sea and Curonian Lagoon) monitoring system in Lithuania. In Lithuania sites, objects, purposes, plans, and activities of the monitoring are included and defined in the national monitoring programme. Monitoring features in Lithuania are also regulated by the Lithuanian Monitoring Act, other relevant national and international treaties, legislation and European Union directives. The majority of information about objects, facilities, and results of monitoring in Lithuania is provided by the Environmental Protection Agency.</gco:CharacterString>      </gmd:abstract> data sets:  1)  meteorological stations network, 2) hydrological stations network, and 3) agrometeorological stations network, data provider – Lithuanian Hydrometeorological Service under the  Ministry of Environment of the Republic of Lithuania; 4) surface water bodies and Baltic Sea monitoring sites and monitoring network, 5) nitrate monitoring stations, and 6) air quality monitoring stations, data provider – Environmental Protection Agency; 7) bathing places and water quality, data provider – the Center for Health Education and Disease Prevention; 8) underground water monitoring facilities and borings, and 9) Seismic monitoring stations, data provider – Lithuanian Geological Survey under the Ministry of Environment of Lithuania.  The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>  </gmd:dataQualityInfo></gmd:MD_Metadata>

</gmd:MD_Identifier>          </gmd:identifier>        </gmd:CI_Citation>      </gmd:citation>      <gmd:abstract>        <gco:CharacterString>According to requirements of Air Quality Directives 2008/50//EC and 2004/107/EC Member States shall establish zones and agglomerations throughout their territory for air quality assessment and management. "Zone" means part of the territory of, as delimited by Member State for the purposes of air quality assessment and management. "Agglomeration" means a zone that is a conurbation with a population in excess of 250 000 inhabitants. Lithuania has established 2 agglomerations (Vilnius and Kaunas) and one zone (the rest territory of Lithuania). Air quality assessment and management shall be carried out in all zones and agglomerations.</gco:CharacterString>      </gmd:abstract>      <gmd:pointOfContact>        <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>       </gmd:CI_Citation>      </gmd:citation>      <gmd:abstract>        <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Human Health and Safety theme represents information about common health indexes and health services statistics in Lithuania, population disease-specific mortality, adults', and school-age children's lifestyle habits, environmental aspects related with human health and safety elements as bathing places, noise values, and road traffic accidents. It is important to mention that the sample of data on adult's lifestyle habits research consists of 24889 surveyed adults aged 18 and over. Data sample on children's lifestyle habits research consists of 38633 surveyed school-aged (5, 7, 9 cl.) children. Data provided by the Lithuanian Ministry of Health and the Center for Health Education and Disease Prevention cover the part ‘the environmental determinant of health’ of the Human Health and Safety theme. Data provided by the Police Department covers the part ‘Safety’ of the Human Health and Safety theme.The objects of the layer HH.HealthDeterminantMeasure.Noise are shown at a scale of 1:5 000.</gco:CharacterString>      </gmd:abstract>      <gmd:pointOfContact>        <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>          <gmd:organisationName>            <gco:CharacterString>SE <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Human Health and Safety theme is created using input data:1) common health indexes and health services statistics, 2) bed account in the hospitals, data provider – the Lithuanian Department of Statistics;3) disease-specific mortality, 4) adults', and 5) school-age children's lifestyle habits, data provider – the Institute of Hygiene;6) bathing places' hygiene, data provider – the Center for Health Education and Disease Prevention;7)noise values, data provider – the Lithuanian Ministry of Health;8)road traffic accidents, data provider – the Police Department. The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>  </gmd:dataQualityInfo></gmd:MD_Metadata>

demographic characteristics for the Lithuanian population and socio-demographic variables grouped by the relevant territorial statistical in Lithuania. <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Population Distribution – Demography theme is created using input data sets provided by the Lithuanian Department of Statistics: 1) demographic characteristics, 2) territorial statistical units, cell size 1x1 km. Provided statistics include 7 demographic characteristics (births, deaths, natural population change, life expectancy, average resident population, median population and resident population) and 5 socio-demographic variables (number of employed people, activity rate, labour force, net international and internal migration) grouped by the relevant territorial statistical unit (by NUTS1, NUTS2, NUTS3, LAU or 1x1 km grid). Also, certain variables are calculated for different gender and/or age groups, certain economic demographic variables – for different economic activities (by NACE classification).The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>  </gmd:dataQualityInfo></gmd:MD_Metadata>

</gmd:citation>      <gmd:abstract>        <gco:CharacterString>Orthoimagery - Annex II.INSPIRE Dataset for Orthoimagery theme contains Lithuanian Digital Raster Orthophotographic Map (ORT10LT at Scale 1:10000) which is created on the background of aerial photography of 2019, 2020 and 2021. Orthophotographic maps can be downloaded as separate sheets in LizardTech MrSID format.The objects are shown at a scale of 1:500 - 1:50 000 through the view service.</gco:CharacterString> <gmd:lineage>        <gmd:LI_Lineage>          <gmd:statement>            <gco:CharacterString>INSPIRE dataset for Soil theme is created using soil data from Spatial data Set of Soil of the Territory of the Republic of Lithuania at scale 1:10 000 (Dirv_DR10LT). The National Land Service under the Ministry of Agriculture is the data provider.National INSPIRE Dataset of Soil Theme consists of four data layers (SoilPlot, SoilBody, SoilHorizon, SoilLayer). SoilPlot (place on which the observation is made) and SoilBody (part of soil body which is homogeneous) data layers have geometry and indicate soil distribution. SoilHorizon and SoilLayer indicate the designation of the soil horizon by The FAO horizon notation and physical characteristics of the soil (for example, depth of the profile element measured from surface).The output data set is created by State Enterprise GIS-Centras, Lithuania.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:statement>        </gmd:LI_Lineage>      </gmd:lineage>    </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>  </gmd:dataQualityInfo></gmd:MD_Metadata>
